title: Grateful Dead Live at Cumberland County Civic Center on 1982-09-17
description:
Set 1

Bertha-> Promised Land, Candyman-> CC Rider, Althea, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Dupree's Diamond Blues, It's All Over Now, West L.A. Fadeaway, Throwing Stones, Deal

Set 2

Touch Of Gray-> Women Are Smarter, High Time, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Spanish Jam-> The Other One-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> Morning Dew-> Sugar Magnolia, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text:
Note says .... The notes of this show say it is an awesome capture. There is not much to add to that . This version is as good as F O B can get. 
 Maybe someone out there has the answer to question I've always wondered about. Why no Mic for Brent on this night. It's the only time it happened. Not just no singing background vocals but no Microphone set up.    
Set list gets 5 stars
sound gets 5 stars
my experience this night gives it 10 stars.
If checking this out for 1st time you will not be disappointed at all.  GREAT job guys
